<TEXT>
here is a chronology of major events in the nancy cruzan 
righttodie case 
jan 11 1983 nancy cruzan then 25 has a wreck on a country 
road southeast of carthage in the ozarks of southwest missouri and 
is thrown from the car paramedics restart her breathing but her 
brain was without oxygen for so long she never regains 
consciousness 
feb 5 1983 doctors implant a feeding tube in ms cruzans 
stomach she isnt on any life support system such as a 
respirator 
oct 19 1983 ms cruzan is moved to the missouri 
rehabilitation center in mount vernon 
oct 23 1987 joe and joyce cruzan ask jasper county probate 
judge charles teel for permission to remove their daughters 
feeding tube so she can die as they believe she would want 
march 9 1988 a threeday hearing begins on the familys 
request the cruzans say their daughter has a commonlaw right to 
be free from unwanted medical treatment and state and federal 
constitutional rights to privacy that protect her right to refuse 
unwanted medical treatment 
july 27 1988 teel approves the request 
aug 3 1988 missouri attorney general william webster files 
notice that the state will appeal to the state supreme court 
nov 16 1988 the state supreme court votes 43 to overturn 
the lower court the family appeals to the us supreme court 
dec 6 1989 the us supreme court hears arguments the 
first time it has considered a righttodie case 
june 25 1990 in a 54 decision the court blocks removal of 
the tube it says the state could keep a patient on life support in 
the absence of clear and convincing evidence the person would 
want to die 
aug 30 1990 ms cruzans parents ask teel for a second 
hearing saying they have new evidence their daughter once 
indicated to three people she would rather die than live in a 
vegetative state 
sept 17 1990 webster says the state no longer has a 
recognizable legal interest in the case and asks the judge to 
drop the state health department and the director of the missouri 
rehabilitation center from future litigation 
oct 23 1990 teel drops the state as a defendant 
nov 1 1990 three former coworkers tell teel they recalled 
conversations with ms cruzan in which she said she never would 
want to live like a vegetable on medical machines ms cruzans 
physician who previously opposed removing the feeding tube terms 
her life a living hell and testifies she should be allowed to 
die 
dec 5 1990 ms cruzans courtappointed guardian recommends 
the tube be removed 
dec 14 1990 teel approves 
dec 1824 1990 state and federal courts reject injunction 
requests by antieuthanasia groups 
dec 26 1990 ms cruzan dies in the missouri rehabilitation 
center 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

