<TEXT>
rep bill frenzel is retiring after 20 years 
in congress a move that mystifies many other lawmakers he 
explains it simply i have grown weary of 90hour weeks 
the 62yearold minnesota republican is leaving capitol hill at 
the peak of what both republicans and democrats call a productive 
house career 
hes highly respected by members on both sides of the aisle 
rep martin sabo dminn said 
as top republican on the house budget committee and one of the 
most outspoken fiscal conservatives on the taxwriting ways and 
means committee frenzel commanded national attention in the 
business community 
he also gained a reputation as one of capitol hills resident 
curmudgeons sometimes seasoning his observations with gentle 
sarcasm 
rep willis gradison rohio recalled that frenzel once 
described himself as a kind of doormat to be walked over by 
ambitious majority members 
i dont think thats true gradison added 
a fiscal conservative but prochoice on abortion frenzel was 
virtually assured of winning reelection for as long as he liked in 
his third district taking in the prosperous southern and western 
suburbs of minneapolis 
but the job proved exasperating at times frenzel said in an 
interview part of it was the grind of early morning breakfasts 
allday meetings and late night sessions on the house floor he 
said with only a touch of exaggeration that added up to 90hour 
weeks 
and these marathon rounds were compounded by agonizing deadlock 
over how to cut the ballooning federal deficit 
the budget was an acute frustration frenzel said i cant 
express how horrible it was over the last six months 
he tried repeatedly without success to impose acrosstheboard 
cuts on spending bills 
in october frenzel put his personal popularity on the line to 
plead with house members to support a deficitreduction package of 
500 billion over five years reached after months of negotiations 
between congressional leaders and the bush administration 
the lawmakers gave him a standing ovation but voted against him 
frenzels favorite targets over the years have included a 
burgeoning federal bureaucracy protectionism in foreign trade 
congressional perquisites and a campaign finance system he deemed 
out of control 
he played a major role in writing campaign finance reform 
legislation following the watergate scandals and was dubbed the 
father of the federal election commission 
the legislation put size limits on political contributions and 
required campaigns to report them to the commission its files in 
turn provide the public with a listing of who gives money to the 
candidates how much and how the funds are spent the measure is 
credited with ending the era in which wealthy fat cats 
bankrolled congressional officeseekers 
frenzel later became an expert in tax policy he fought 
successfully in 1978 and 1981 for cuts in the capital gains tax he 
believed would stimulate economic growth 
in 1990 after years of trying he got the house to impose 
limits on free congressional mail what frenzel called the last 
black hole of congress 
just what comes next is uncertain 
frenzel said he would like to become a political analyst or 
resident sage with a think tank or a private company 
but he did not rule out a bush administration post and his name 
has come up in connection with the position of us trade 
representative the incumbent carla hills has been mentioned as a 
possible successor to pete wilson who is leaving the senate to be 
governor of california 
many former members of congress who like frenzel do not want to 
leave washington wind up staying on capitol hill as lobbyists 
but frenzel plainspoken as usual said that was out of the 
question 
if i dont want to be the dog he said i dont know why 
id want to be the tail of the dog 
</TEXT>
