the agriculture department is recalling 502 
pounds of canadian kosher frankfurters from a monsey ny retail 
store after federal inspectors found contamination by food 
poisoning organisms 
usda authorities said wednesday that the store the meat 
showcase is cooperating in the recall of continental strictly 
kosher beef frankfurters made in montreal canada 
it is the only store in the united states that has received the 
product said the departments food safety and inspection service 
the 14ounce packages are labeled product of canada and bear 
the crown inspection seal of canada they also bear the mark 
establishment number 472 and have no sellby date 
the problem was discovered by usda inspectors in a routine 
import reinspection in buffalo ny 
ronald j prucha associated administrator of the usda agency 
said no illnesses have been reported he said consumers should 
return the suspected franks to the place of purchase 
the suspected bacteria can cause listeriosis which was 
described as a rare but potentially serious disease 
listeriosis is believed to pose little risk for healthy 
people the agency said but it said those with weakened immune 
systems including infants the elderly and the chronically ill are 
most vulnerable 
symptoms in adults include the sudden onset of flulike symptoms 
such as fever chills headache backache and sometimes abdominal 
pain and diarrhea newborns can exhibit respiratory distress 
refusal to drink and vomiting 
consumers with questions about the recall can phone the 
departments tollfree hot line at 18005354555 between 10 am 
est and 4 pm est monday through friday taped information will 
be available at other times 
callers in the washington dc metropolitan area can call 202 
4473333 
