police marksmen went looking for foxes and 
wild dogs on wednesday as authorities began trying to curb an 
outbreak of rabies that has left one 8yearold boy dead 
the outbreak also has killed camals and other tribal livestock 
and it is believed to be centered in northern oman near villages 
surrounding ibri 200 miles from the capital 
the boy who died of the disease was the first documented case of 
human rabies infection in the sultunate 
a task force from the world health organization will work with 
state health and agricultural officials to try to stop the spread 
of the disease 
as part of the effort police will shoot wild dogs and other 
animals that can carry the disease 
ministry of health spokesman ms elbualy said the situation 
has been a matter of concern but it is under control 
we are looking into methods of introducing oral bait 
containing a vaccine which will enable these wild populations in 
effect to vaccinate themselves against rabies and to prevent 
further spread of the disease he said 
