<TEXT>
an israeli newspaper reported today that 
secretary of state james a baker iii will likely meet saddam 
hussein in baghdad for talks on jan 9 but a us official said no 
date for any negotiations had been set 
the independent daily maariv attributed the report to accounts 
reaching jerusalem from israeli diplomats based ontheir talks 
with us colleagues 
but in washington state department spokeswoman sondra mccarty 
said there was no such agreement on talks aimed at resolving the 
persian gulf crisis 
our embassy in baghdad is in almost daily contact with the 
iraqi foreign ministry there has been no iraqi movement on the 
question of dates she said she declined to elaborate 
israels foreign ministry said it had no information on any 
meeting between baker and the iraqi president prime minister 
yitzhak shamirs spokesman avi pazner also said he had no 
knowledge of such a proposal 
ruth yaron spokeswoman for the israeli embassy in washington 
also said we have no knowledge of anything of the sort she 
called the newspaper report pure speculation 
maariv said the meeting was set amid apparent secret 
negotiations between the united states and iraq 
the iraqi president has said for months that any resolution of 
the gulf crisis should be linked to a settlement of the 
israelipalestinian conflict saddam has recalled his ambassadors 
from the united states the united nations and several western 
european nations in past days giving rise to speculation that a 
new diplomatic initiative was in the works 
the paper said senior officials in washington told israeli 
representatives that baker would agree to visit baghdad on jan 9 
despite its proximity to the jan 15 united nations ultimatum for 
an iraqi troop pullout from kuwait 
saddam has previously offered to receive baker in baghdad on 
jan 12 but the white house has rejected that date as being too 
late it has said any date after jan 3 would not be acceptable 
saddam is also said to be demanding that the un security 
council pass a resolution linking iraqi withdrawal from kuwait to a 
settlement of the palestinian issue the israeli newspaper hadashot 
quoted the jordanian daily al shaab as saying saddam would announce 
such a plan in the next few days 
the united states and israel both have opposed any linkage 
between the iraqs aug 2 seizure of kuwait and israels 23year 
occupation of the west bank and gaza strip 
maariv said a jan 9 bakersaddam meeting could be linked to 
plans by a top aide to baker dennis ross to visit israel on jan 
7 to discuss new middle east peace proposals 
the foreign ministry spokesman said ross was expected to come to 
israel on jan 7 or 9 
the state department appears to be putting together a proposal 
for opening peace talks between israel and arab countries in tandem 
with holding municipal elections for 17 million palestinians in 
the occupied territories maariv said 
maariv also reported military movement along israels border 
with jordan and israels chief of staff lt gen dan shomron 
warned iraq may try to use jordan as a springboard for action 
against israel 
shomron said in a statement broadcast on israeli radio stations 
that jordan was liable to find itself despite its will or that 
of its leaders caught up in iraqi moves 
an army spokesman declined comment on the reported military 
moves along the jordan frontier the military routinely refuses 
comment on reports of military maneuvers 
the spokesman whose name cannot be used under army regulations 
added there was no change in the armys level of alert since a 
