a dozen years ago cities enjoyed the same broad immunity as 
states against such lawsuits but a 1978 us supreme court 
decision opened the floodgates 
the court said cities their agencies and city officials may be 
sued for violating an individuals civil rights damages could be 
awarded if the violation occurred while a city ordinance or 
official policy was being followed 
