former deputy solicitor general andrew l frey 
will handle appeals for the office of irancontra independent 
counsel lawrence e walsh the office announced wednesday 
he will be responsible for arguing against the appeal by former 
national security adviser john m poindexter and for continuing the 
appellate proceedings against former nsc aide oliver l north 
frey 52 was deputy solicitor general from 1973 to 1986 and 
gained public attention for successfully appealing the convictions 
against lyn nofziger the onetime political director for former 
president reagan 
poindexter is appealing his five convictions of april 7 one 
count of conspiring to obstruct inquiries and proceedings two 
counts of obstructing congress and two counts of false statements 
north was convicted may 4 of three counts altering and 
destroying official documents accepting an illegal gratuity and 
aiding and abetting in the obstruction of congress but those 
convictions were vacated by a threejudge panel of the us court 
of appeals for the district of columbia on july 20 one conviction 
was reversed outright while the others were simply vacated for 
further proceedings a petition by the prosecutor for a rehearing 
of the appeal by the full court was denied 
walshs office has not yet decided whether to petition the 
supreme court to overturn the appellate panels decision but such 
a petition would be due near the end of february frey said 
frey is a partner in the washington office of the chicagobased 
law firm mayer brown amp platt 
nofziger was convicted in february 1988 on three felony counts 
of illegally lobbying former white house colleagues within a year 
of resigning as reagans political director in early 1982 those 
charges were brought by independent counsel james c mckay 
frey argued the appeal in november 1988 and the appeals court 
overturned the nofziger convictions in june 1989 mckay decided 
last december to drop the case after the supreme court refused to 
reinstate the conviction 
frey will not join walshs office on a fulltime basis but will 
be paid per diem 
