<TEXT>
king michael romanias former monarch returned 
to exile in switzerland wednesday after being expelled by the 
bucharest government less than 12 hours after he arrived in his 
homeland on his first visit in 43 years 
the 69yearold former king returned to romania one year after 
the execution of communist dictator nicolae ceausescu in a popular 
revolution the communist takeover in 1947 forced the monarch into 
exile 
the bucharest government called michaels brief visit a cheap 
sensation government spokesman bogdan baltazar said in a 
statement that michaels presence in romania was totally 
illegal 
the romanian government facing mounting strikes and protests by 
an opposition that accuses it of being a communist regime in 
disguise apparently had feared the visit by michael might stir up 
unrest it threw him out on grounds he had not secured permission 
to visit 
in bucharest wednesday about 300 protesters marched up the main 
boulevard shouting king michael king michael the opposition 
civic alliance called for a referendum on restoring romanias 
former constitutional monarchy 
the statement also urged parliament to condemn the expulsion and 
invite michael back 
