would take up his post only if geagea and saadeh join the 
government nadim salem a catholic who was appointed minister of 
public works also said he would not join the government unless 
phalangists and the lebanese forces end their boycott 
geagea and saadeh have said the dominant representation of 
prosyrian factions in the new cabinet implies it has been dictated 
by syria both called it a fait accompli government 
syria is lebanons main power broker it has 40000 troops 
stationed in northern eastern and central lebanon under a 1976 
peacekeeping mandate from the arab league 
but the arab league last year sponsored a special session of the 
lebanese parliament in the saudi town of taif that approved a peace 
plan based on moslemchristian equal powersharing 
the plan also calls for the disbanding of lebanons militias by 
march 21 and for the syrian army to gradually withdraw from beirut 
and major towns over the next two years and redeploy in east 
lebanons bekaa valley 
geagea and saadeh contend they represent the major christian 
fighting forces and that no national reconciliation is possible 
without their participation as the main christian negotiators 
president elias hrawi a maronite and karami a sunni moslem 
have tried both directly and through intermediaries to persuade 
geagea and saadeh to join the new government 
karami has to present his cabinet to parliament next week to 
seek a vote of confidence 
seven christian and moslem warlords have been appointed state 
ministers without portfolios in the new cabinet to gain their 
approval of a plan to disarm and disband their militias 
geageas 6000member lebanese forces control more than 70 
percent of lebanons christian heartland north and northeast of 
beirut 
