second of his works to be inducted into the hall of fame his 
recording of in the mood was inducted in 1983 miller recorded 
moonlight serenade which helped the miller band to a top spot 
among american dance bands in 1939 
show boat recorded by jerome kern in 1932 was the first 
album of show music recorded in the united states the voices of 
paul robeson and helen morgan are among those on the album 
the original cast album of leonard bernsteins west side 
story was produced and released in 1957 it featured carol 
lawrence and larry kert 
