<TEXT>
the 1991 toyota tercel 2door deluxe is not your basic econobox 
it has a remarkaby smoothshifting fivespeed manual 
transmission 
it has contemporary rounded exterior styling and clean modern 
interior 
and it doesnt have a hatchback sibling for 1991 toyota 
eliminated the hatchback design thats standard fare at the low end 
of the car market and decided to offer the tercel in upscale 2and 
4door sedan models that have trunks 
we want to keep toyota buyers for the long haul so we dont 
punish them in their first experience with us said bob mccurry 
toyota executive vice president 
the tercels starting price of 6488 also is noteworthy its 
unchanged from the previous model year and makes the new tercel the 
lowest price car with a trunk in america it compares with the 
6995 honda civic 3door the 7999 nissan sentra and the 6597 
daihatsu charade 3door 
the aps test tercel a 2door with a base price of 7798 
performed well it wasnt a barn burner what with its 15liter 
inline 12valve fourcylinder engine capable of producing 82 
horsepower at 5200 rpm i also had to really push the clutch to 
the floor so the key would activate the ignition 
but the car does accelerate faster than the previous tercel 
model and the fuel economy of 29 miles per gallon in the city and 
35 mpg on the highway was appreciated it was a pleasure too to 
note the fine mating of the transmission with the engine i rarely 
felt a jerk as i shifted gears 
there was some road noise but not as much as might be expected 
toyota added extra sounddeadening material thats also used on the 
camry and worked to minimize vibration 
the cars suspension macpherson strut in front and a torsion 
beam in back was decent and took bumps and turns quite well 
fit and finish were superb toyota has reduced the size of body 
panel gaps on the exterior 
the interior was spartan though not necessarily cheaplooking 
ventilation ducts were modern and round and could be turned easily 
and directed for maximum effect gauges were large and easy to 
read 
as expected the cars equipment was basic the vehicle did not 
have power windows power locks a clock tilt steering or a remote 
trunk lid release and the rear windows do not open the trunk 
floor had a vinyl cover but there was nothing to cover the bare 
metal on the interior trunk sides 
the floor mats were a 55 option and power steering a real 
help in tight turns in parking lots cost 250 
the car had seat belts for five but the middle person in back 
sits up quite high on an awkward though cushioned resting spot 
i was glad to see that legroom in back was ok if the front seats 
are up a ways but my knees were pushed into the seatbacks when the 
seats were all the way back on their tracks toyota said the new 
tercel has 9 percent more interior space than its predecessor with 
an average of 1 inch added to each interior dimension 
the automaker looks to sell 130000 of the 1991 tercels which 
were introduced in november that would be up from approximately 
100000 for the 1990 model tercel 
the tercel has been in the united states since 1980 and has 
averaged about 100000 sales a year spokesman jim fewel said 
