<TEXT>
orange juice futures prices spurted higher wednesday on the new 
york cotton exchange reflecting worries that heavy frost damage to 
the california orange crop will hurt juice supplies 
on other markets precious metal futures surged along with crude 
oil livestock and meat futures were mostly higher and grains and 
soybeans advanced 
frozen concentrated orange juice futures settled 17 cents to 
39 cents higher with the contract for delivery in january at 
1181 a pound 
the rally marked the fifth straight trading day of gains for 
most orange juice futures the january contracts price soared 
about 12 percent last week in anticipation of frost damage to 
oranges over the christmas weekend 
extremely cold temperatures on friday saturday and sunday 
nights damaged most of the california navel orange crop the 
nations main source of fresh oranges 
floridas orange crop which is used mainly for juice escaped 
the freeze but the disaster in california means a larger share of 
the florida crop probably will end up in supermarket produce 
sections analysts said 
i believe we will need to bring in oranges from florida for 
the fresh market said celeste georkakis an orange juice analyst 
with cargill investor services inc 
conversely some of the damaged california oranges will be 
processed into frozen juice concentrate she said but that must be 
done quickly to avoid spoilage 
the whole question is how much they can process in a short 
period of time because theyre not geared to processing as much as 
florida where 90 percent of the crop ends up as juice georkakis 
said 
unusually cold weather is expected to return to southern 
california this weekend according to the national weather service 
analysts said few traders were willing to sell oj futures ahead of 
another long holiday weekend with the threat of further crop damage 
in the air 
oil and precious metals futures rose sharply amid increasing 
fears of a middle east war 
the rising tensions partly reflected us and iraqi officials 
inability to agree on a meeting date before the jan 15 deadline 
set by the united nations for withdrawal of iraqi troops from 
kuwait 
on the new york mercantile exchange light sweet crude oil 
futures settled 60 cents to 130 higher with february at 2722 a 
barrel heating oil was 16 cents to 232 cents higher with january 
at 8126 cents a gallon unleaded gasoline was 155 cents to 19 
cents higher with january at 6814 cents a gallon natural gas was 
