<TEXT>
president roh taewoos appointment 
thursday of americaneducated lee bongsuh as trade and industry 
minister is seen as an effort to mend trade frictions between seoul 
and washington 
the appointment was the only economic post changed in a cabinet 
shakeup that included a the naming of a new prime minister and 
foreign minister 
the new trade minister is considered knowledgeable in us 
affairs having studied at american universities and worked in 
washington observers hope he will be able to heal animosities 
between the two longtime allies on trade matters 
the united states is south koreas largest trading partner 
washington has pressured seoul to open its markets wider to foreign 
goods and farm products 
the seoul government claims foreign imports will hurt the 
competitiveness of korean goods and threaten the livelihood of 
korean workers radical students and farmers have staged violent 
protests demanding a halt to us trade pressure 
lee 54 is a 1959 graduated of the university of pennsylvania 
and received a doctorate in economics from harvard in 1965 he 
worked in washington during the 1960s for the us federal reserve 
and the world bank 
he returned to south korea in the early 1970s and entered a long 
term of government service 
